This paper discusses clustering, which is a common topic in machine learning and data mining. The paper specifically focuses on the robustness of clustering algorithms to perturbations in the data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also touches on natural language processing (NLP) and database systems, which could place it in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.DB (Databases) sub-categories, respectively.
